She looked at him.
"Sorry commander...err...I mean, sorry Scorponok. I didn't mean to make you 
angry."
She smiled.  She placed her hand on his cheek and slowly glided her hand 
down his cheek and over his neck. She leaned forward and kisses him again.  
She was enjoying that energy running through her spark when she kissed him.  
She felt something inside her that she had never felt before and if felt 
wonderful to her.  She wanted to be with him.  She never wanted to leave his 
side. "We can go for a wak in the forest if that will make you happy."
She smiled at him.  Her spark was his and she knew it.
